# Reduce build context size.
#
# `scripts/*` (not `scripts/`) excludes every direct child of scripts/ —
# files and subdirectory ENTRIES — but leaves the parent directory itself
# present, so a negation rule below can re-include a single file. Excluding
# `scripts/` outright would mean buildkit could not re-include
# `scripts/migrate-from-secrets.js` (per Docker .dockerignore semantics:
# "not possible to re-include a file if a parent directory is excluded").
# Subdirectory contents are skipped transitively because their parent
# directory entry is excluded.
#
# `migrations/` (48 KB) is needed in full by docker/backend.Dockerfile:70
# and is removed from the exclude list entirely — the size cost is
# negligible and there are no future scenarios where we'd add an
# image-irrelevant file under that path.
#
# Without these adjustments the buildx step fails with
# "failed to calculate checksum ... not found" because the COPYs at
# backend.Dockerfile:70-71 reference paths the daemon never received.
# Regressed silently from commit b50a37fb (2026-05-29) which added the
# two COPYs without updating .dockerignore; blocked every push to main
# from 2026-05-29 through 2026-05-31.
docs/
scripts/*
ecs/
certs/
.claude/
.github/

!scripts/migrate-from-secrets.js
